  <!-- ═══════════════ PROJECT CONTENT ═══════════════ -->
  <div class="project-content">
    <div class="project-layout">

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <main class="project-main">

        <div class="proj-section">
          <span class="proj-section-label">Overview</span>
          <h2 class="proj-section-title">Project Overview</h2>
          <p>
            The Co-op Education Platform is a comprehensive web application developed to support university cooperative education programs. It digitalizes the entire co-op process — from students browsing and applying for placements, to supervisors managing student progress, to faculty advisors tracking academic requirements and outcomes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Built with TypeScript on the frontend and Go on the backend, the system handles multi-role workflows with different access levels and responsibilities for each participant type.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="proj-section">
          <span class="proj-section-label">Problem Statement</span>
          <h2 class="proj-section-title">The Problem</h2>
          <p>
            Co-op education programs typically involve three-way coordination between students, host companies, and universities — a process historically managed through emails, spreadsheets, and manual document submissions. This leads to:
          </p>
          <ul class="proj-feature-list">
            <li>Difficulty tracking which students are placed, where, and at what stage of their co-op</li>
            <li>Inconsistent evaluation processes across different company supervisors</li>
            <li>Faculty advisors lacking visibility into student progress mid-placement</li>
            <li>Students struggling to find and apply for suitable placements</li>
            <li>Missed deadlines for reports, evaluations, and sign-offs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="proj-section">
          <span class="proj-section-label">Solution Approach</span>
          <h2 class="proj-section-title">How I Solved It</h2>
          <p>
            I contributed to building a multi-role platform with distinct workflows for each participant type:
          </p>
          <ul class="proj-feature-list">
            <li>Designed a RESTful API backend in Go with clean separation of concerns and role-aware endpoints</li>
            <li>Built a TypeScript/JavaScript frontend providing role-specific dashboards and workflows</li>
            <li>Modeled the relational database in SQL to represent placements, evaluations, timelines, and document submissions</li>
            <li>Implemented student-facing placement browsing, application, and status tracking</li>
            <li>Created supervisor evaluation forms and mid-term/final assessment workflows</li>
            <li>Built faculty advisor panels for monitoring all active students and placement metrics</li>
            <li>Developed notification and deadline reminder systems for key milestones</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="proj-section">
          <span class="proj-section-label">Key Features</span>
          <h2 class="proj-section-title">Key Features</h2>
          <ul class="proj-feature-list">
            <li>Three-role system: Student, Company Supervisor, Faculty Advisor</li>
            <li>Placement listing with company profiles, role descriptions, and application management</li>
            <li>Structured evaluation forms with rubric-based assessment criteria</li>
            <li>Document submission portal for student reports and supervisor sign-offs</li>
            <li>Timeline and deadline tracking with automated notification reminders</li>
            <li>Faculty dashboard with aggregate placement statistics and student status overview</li>
            <li>Placement history and GPA/performance correlation reporting</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="proj-section">
          <span class="proj-section-label">Result / Impact</span>
          <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results &amp; Impact</h2>
          <div class="result-highlight">
            <p>
              The platform <strong>unified the co-op process across all three stakeholder groups</strong> into a single digital workflow, eliminating the coordination overhead of email chains and manual tracking. Students experienced a <strong>streamlined application and placement process</strong>, while faculty advisors gained full visibility into placement outcomes and student performance metrics for <strong>program improvement planning</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </main>

